The '''Belarusian Women's Handball Championship''' is the premier [[league (sports)|league]] for women's [[team handball|handball]] clubs in [[Belarus]]. First held in 1993 following the [[collapse of the Soviet Union]], it has been dominated since by [[BNTU Minsk]], formerly known as Politechnik Minsk and No. 6 Minsk.<ref>[http://handball.by/%D0%98%D1%81%D1%82%D0%BE%D1%80%D0%B8%D1%8F-%D1%87%D0%B5%D0%BC%D0%BF%D0%B8%D0%BE%D0%BD%D0%B0%D1%82%D0%BE%D0%B2-%D0%A0%D0%91/%D0%90%D1%80%D1%85%D0%B8%D0%B2.html 1993–2011 tables] in the Belarusian Handball Association's website</ref>
