'''Karang language''' (also called '''Mbum East''' or '''Lakka''') is an [[Mbum languages|Mbum language]] of [[Cameroon]].
== Writing system== {|class="wikitable" |+Karang alphabet |- ! Uppercase | A || B || Ɓ || D || Ɗ | E || F || G || GB || H | I || K || KP || L || M | MB || MGB || N || ND || NZ | Ŋ || ŊG || O || Ɔ || P | R || S || T || U || V | VB || W || Y || Ƴ || Z |- ! Lowercase | a || b || ɓ || d || ɗ | e || f || g || gb || h | i || k || kp || l || m | mb || mgb || n || nd || nz | ŋ || ŋg || o || ɔ || p | r || s || t || u || v | vb || w || y || ƴ || z |}
Nasalisation is indicated with a cedilla : a̧, ȩ, i̧, o̧, ɔ̧, u̧.
The only tone is high, indicated with an acute accent: á, é, í, ó, ɔ́, ú; it can be combined with nasalisation: á̧, ȩ́, í̧, ó̧, ú̧.
Long vowels are indicated with an h.
