The '''Grand Miroslav Zei Award''' ({{lang-sl|Velika nagrada Miroslava Zeia}}) is a scientific award in [[Slovenia]] awarded each year for outstanding scientific achievements in Biology. It has been bestowed since 2010 by the [[National Institute of Biology]] and includes a prize for achievements in research at the Institute and a grand award for achievements in Life and Environmental Sciences.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nib.si/index.php/aktualno/novice/369-sveani-dogodek-ob-50-obletnici-delovanja-nib-potekal-pod-astnim-pokroviteljstvom-g-boruta-pahorja-predsednika-vlade-rs.html|title=Novice|author=Irena|work=nib.si|accessdate=12 December 2014}}</ref>
It is named after [[Miroslav Zei]], the eminent Slovene biologist.
